    "texts": [
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Identification features",
            "shortText": "<p>Low, many-stemmed shrub growing to about 1 m and with long, stems that bear small, fat, oblong leaves in four ranks pressed closely against the stem. Tips of stems woolly. Flowers yellow to pink, in spikes, anthers protrude from the flowers. Fruit attractive, round red berries.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_1_9685",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Adult size",
            "shortText": "<p>Plants up to about 1 m tall, leaves about 3 mm long.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_2_9686",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Distribution",
            "shortText": "<p><u>Global:</u> Endemic to South Africa.</p><p><u>Local/Regional:</u> Restricted distribution in Southwestern Cape from about Melkbosstrand to Bredasdorp district.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_3_9687",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Biology",
            "shortText": "<p>Found on coastal dunes and between rocks along the coast. The berries are eaten by tortoises and are attractive to birds which play an important role in seed distribution. Has an extensive root system and is a useful plant for dune stabilization. Also popular in coastal gardens.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_4_9688",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Food / prey",
            "shortText": "<p>Photosynthetic.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_5_9689",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Reproduction",
            "shortText": "<p>Flowers October to November. Wind pollinated.&nbsp;</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_6_9690",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Similar species",
            "shortText": "<p>Fairly unmistakable.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_7_9691",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        }
